Troubleshooting Tips
SpiderFoot won't start:

Check if port 5001 is already in use: netstat -tuln | grep 5001
Verify Python dependencies: pip3 install -r requirements.txt
Check permissions on /opt/spiderfoot directory
recon-ng module errors:

Reinstall modules: marketplace install all in recon-ng console
Check internet connectivity for module downloads
Verify workspace exists: workspaces list
Pipeline scripts fail:

Ensure scripts are executable: chmod +x /opt/*.py
Check Python path: which python3
Verify target domain format (must include TLD)
Review error messages in output files
No results generated:

Check output directory permissions
Verify target is reachable: ping <target>
Increase timeout values in configuration
Check firewall rules if running remotely
